# childwaf blocklist – DNS-over-HTTPS (DoH) Provider IP Ranges
#
# Blocking connections to these IPs prevents children from bypassing domain
# filtering by using encrypted DNS (DoH on port 443).
#
# NOTE: These are IP addresses / CIDR ranges, not domain names.
#       This file is loaded into a hash:net ipset, not processed by dnsmasq.
#       Reference it in a child profile with:
#         BLOCK_CATEGORIES="... doh-providers"
#
# Keep this list updated – providers add and rotate IPs periodically.
# Last reviewed: 2026-01

# ── Google (8.8.8.8 / dns.google) ────────────────────────────────────────────
8.8.8.8/32
8.8.4.4/32
2001:4860:4860::8888/128
2001:4860:4860::8844/128

# ── Cloudflare (1.1.1.1 / cloudflare-dns.com) ────────────────────────────────
1.1.1.1/32
1.0.0.1/32
1.1.1.2/32
1.0.0.2/32
1.1.1.3/32
1.0.0.3/32
2606:4700:4700::1111/128
2606:4700:4700::1001/128

# ── Quad9 (9.9.9.9) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
9.9.9.9/32
149.112.112.112/32
2620:fe::fe/128
2620:fe::9/128

# ── OpenDNS / Cisco ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
208.67.222.222/32
208.67.220.220/32
208.67.222.123/32
208.67.220.123/32

# ── AdGuard DNS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
94.140.14.14/32
94.140.15.15/32

# ── NextDNS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
45.90.28.0/24
45.90.30.0/24
